          <msContents>
            <summary>Lecture notes on 'De coelo', 'De generatione et corruptione', 'Meteorologica', 'De anima' and 'Parva naturalia': with 'Quaestiones variae'. Contents: (1) In libros de coelo questiones. 'Finis ... Die 2, Martis. 1575.' (ff. 1-20.) (2) Librorum de generationis et corruptionis tractione explanatio. 'Finis ... die 28 Maii.' 1575. (ff. 21-90.) (3) De rebus metereologicis [sic] tractatus. With 2 'Tabellae'. (ff. 91-112.) (4) Librorum de anima explicationes. [Finis] 'die 9 Septembris.' 1575. (ff. 113-186.) (5) Eorum quae Parva naturalia appeallantur brevis explicatio. 'Finem imposuimus die 19 mensis Septembris.' 1575. (ff. 187-199.) (6) Quaestiones variae. These notes seem to be in the same hand as that of the writer of the notes of lectures on Hippocrates' 'Aphorisms' by Bernardino Trivisano at Padua in 1579-1580 (MS. No. 507), and of the fragments 'DE sanguinis missione', etc. (MS. No. 508). Produced in [Padua?].</summary>
